    {
      "op_id": "OP-068",
      "operation": "schema_investigation_note",
      "description": "ATTENTION CLAUDE CODE — DB_ONLY_PROTECTED classification correction. The following 7 terms were classified as extracted in a prior session and are marked DB_ONLY_PROTECTED: H0637 (aph, also), H0859A (attah, you m.s.), H1697G (davar, word), H1961 (hayah, to be), H2063 (zot, this), H5973A (im, with), H8033G (sham, there). All are high-frequency grammatical function words (HFA). Diagnostic analysis confirms their exported verses have 0-6% overlap with actual covenant verses (H1285 berith / G1242 diatheke) — they are collocational bleed from the Phase 1 extraction, not covenant vocabulary. The researcher has reviewed this finding and authorised reclassification to delete. These terms must be updated to status=delete despite the DB_ONLY_PROTECTED flag. This instruction constitutes the researcher override required to clear that protection. Please also investigate why the Phase 1 extraction routine included these grammatical particles as standalone covenant vocabulary entries, and report findings."
    },
